<br>
Do you know that RNG stands for Random Number Generator? That means you aren't guaranteed a MP if you make 50 items. In fact, the chance of going 300 tries without getting a MP is 0.23%. One in 434 times someone tries for a MP it will take them over 300 attempts. When you take a look at all the crafters out there it's not going to take long before someone whines about the broken RNG (like you).<br>
<br>
200 attempts: 1.76%<br>
100 attempts: 13.26%<br>
50 attempts: 36.42%<br>
<br>
Over 1/3 of your MP tries with a perfect RNG will take more than 50 attempts.  <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whorde>whorde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/23/03 12:11:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=583.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: trinketing</span><hr size=1> on the counting cards note i've been trying that with making 99s.  add one for each time you make a 94 to 98, subtract 6 if you get a 99.  theoretically when your number got above +6 you should start making armor.<br>
