<br>
But I will tell you this.  TRy making trinkets until you make a MP.  Then count the number of times it takes to the next mp.  If your number is less than 20-30 (yes it is variable), then keep making trinkets until the next cycle.  Then you start making your armor/weapons.  Oh, and the making of chain/stud/weapon haft etc counts towards the cycle.  It is highly subjective and depends on many variables- like current population of crafters.  I noticed recently that the more crafters on, the less skilling you will do, or see streaks that are much lower odds than 1 in 9.  I craft solely in the morning since I noticed that and did from 1000-1102 in 2 weeks.  I spent the evening farming the gold/arcanium to pay for it too.<br>
<br>
To Gisborne- Computers dont generate random numbers.  They generate pseudo random numbers- so you will get patterns, even in an environment like DAoC. It is a matter of observation, and determination.  Frankly, the whole issue of is it 2% on each try or 2% on 10000 is hogwash.  you are not looking at the statistical mean over large attempts.  That will be 2 %.  What you look at is the trends in each window of sampling.  So if you make 2000 hinges and 100 armor pieces, you still get the 2% average.  But, it is possible to hit the statistical anomalies in the computer numbers during each window of attempts.  That is not inconsistent with the whole 2% RNG numbers.<br>
<br>
Besides, I dont really care if you say it doesnt work or not.  I just look at the 14 99Qs and 3 Mps that I made in those 37 tries and just chuckle to myself. And that is my argument.  No science involved.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amstellight>Amstel Light</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/23/03 2:41:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=583.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Posting math???</span><hr size=1> Doh, I meant to direct that question to Gisborne regarding is probabilities of success/failure.  Its a basic Binomial Distribution, but I forget how that is done.  Sorry to direct it at you Kilgour.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
